==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: In-and-in
<hw>In"-and-in"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>An old game played
with four dice. <xex>In</xex> signified a doublet, or two dice alike;
<xex>in-and-in</xex>, either two doubles, or the four dice
alike.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>In and in</ent>⟦br⟧
